<subSubSection box="[192,707,511,535]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="41.[192,707,511,535]" box="[192,707,511,535]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<heading bold="true" box="[192,707,511,535]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,707,511,535]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[192,487,511,535]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oenides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,301,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Oenides</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
is a valid genus
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[192,1440,560,683]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName box="[232,442,560,584]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpina">
<emphasis box="[232,442,560,584]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Hesperia vulpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. and R. Felder, 1867 is not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1040,1202,560,584]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[1040,1202,560,584]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Alera furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1264,1317,561,585]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[192,258,593,617]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,258,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Alera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where 
<taxonomicName box="[357,488,593,617]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpina">
<emphasis box="[357,488,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">H. vulpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously placed, and since it is the 
<typeStatus box="[1007,1060,594,618]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
species of the available genusgroup name 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[341,611,625,650]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oenides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[341,438,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Oenides</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
, that was considered a subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1157,1223,625,649]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1157,1223,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Alera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we resurrect this genus from synonymy and use it as a monotypic valid genus with the species 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1325,658,682]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oenides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpina">
<emphasis box="[1127,1325,658,682]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Oenides vulpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1340,1426,659,683]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[192,1440,213,1528]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 13. Genomic trees of Hesperiina, Pericharini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
